gujarati.context:
I describe my own state, I don't know what; 
The lord's mercy is great, they say it brings compassion.

Note: "કહું" means "I" or "me", but in this context, it seems to mean "my own state" or "what I feel".

Here is the translation:

Where Maharaj's majesty is seen, that is extremely happy and auspicious;
He has been satisfied with a glance; I have not found joy in examination.

Here is the translation:

This is all the talk of my town, I have enjoyed good company; 
People say, blessed Prabhu Das, you have gone to God's place.

This is the translation:

See so much divine beauty, I am amazed as if seeing; 
If we see Maharaja's bravery, He says from where He says like this.
